{
  "stem": "21310.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, like, 2/3 of the room and put some sheets on there for privacy because people who were going into the kitchen-- and everybody had to share the kitchen-- were going through-- through that room.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so there was constant traffic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every room was occupied.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I remember this-- this wire and the sheets there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And and-- and that's where we stayed for a while.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We-- we made some house committees where people were organizing food for people who didn't have it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember a so-called 'spoon' campaign where you would go from apartment to apartment and ask for a spoon of sugar, a spoon of groats, a spoon of flour.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you would bring that to a-- a soup kitchen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And some apartment houses, the women themselves, they would cook and make the soup or whatever for people who were completely out of things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Actually, the worst fate [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] was I had the-- the worst off were-- were the refugees from such surrounding communities because they, to start with, most of them were poor, and they could only come in with what they could carry.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they came a little bit later, so they couldn't get rooms and apartments so shelters were established.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so people were in the shelters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in some places, they-- they couldn't even get into a shelter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they bedded down in basements and in attics.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And these people were the first ones to really die of hunger.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But the soup kitchens were established in-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
